title: Snub rhombicuboctahedron
summary: The snub rhombicuboctahedron is a polyhedron, constructed as a truncated rhombicuboctahedron. It has 74 faces: 18 squares, and 56 triangles. It can also be called the Conway snub cuboctahedron in but will be confused with the Coxeter snub cuboctahedron, the snub cube.
